At first, it was thought that the Ukrainian war developed as the biblical account of David and Goliath, but&nbsp; Russia demonstrated "not to be an invincible subject". The Italian premier Mario Draghi <a href="https://www.agi.it/estero/news/2022-05-11/draghi-russia-non-golia-pace-non-sia-set-16698863/">expresses words of optimism </a>dopo&nbsp; the meeting yesterday and that went "very well" &nbsp; with the President of the United States With Biden, a tuning of views has been reached on the negotiating path that is "very difficult" and "the first point is how to build it". In any case, "there must not be a peace imposed nor&nbsp; by a type of allies nor&nbsp; by others," he adds.
For the President of the Council, it is necessary to bring "all parts" to the table and suggest where to start: "The unblocking of grain from Ukrainian ports can be a proof of dialogue."
On the diplomatic front are ongoing negotiations between Moscow and Kiev, which proposed to the Russians &nbsp; an exchange between injured Ukrainian prisoners and fighters trapped in Azvostal steel mills in Mariupol. It was reported on Telegram by the Ukrainian Deputy Premier, Iryna Vereshchuk.&nbsp;
Russian forces are attacking the Azovstal steel mill in Mariupol not only with hunting and artillery, but also with tanks. Unkriform reports, which published a photo showing a column of black smoke rising from the site, where a fire broke out.
All civilians who had found refuge in the Azvostal steel mill in Mariupol were evacuated. Captain Svyatoslav Palamar, Deputy Commander of the Azov Regiment, told Cnn, however, that it is difficult to make a complete assessment of the situation throughout the enormous structure.
The fights between Russian troops are continuing, trying to conquer the East and the south of the country and the Ukrainian ones who resist and in some cases turn back the attack, as happened in the area around Kharkiv.
