Macron's strategy against the left opening on Le Monde, which looks at the June legislative elections and focuses on the president's moves. Because, underlined the newspaper, the presidentials fought against the right of Marine Le Pen, but now the opponent is the unitary cartel of the gauche put together by Jean-Luc Melenchon, and therefore the tactics must be completely different. Macron, in a meeting with the Columns of his party La Republique en marche, has indicated that he aims to attract the Social-Democratic electorate by insisting on the anti-Europeanism of Melenchon, which has brought into the program of his coalition the "disobedience" to the European treaties. But the ace in the sleeve, it previews the newspaper, will be the aids against the carovita, that the next government will have to hurry to pass before the vote, to remove to the left its main propagandistic argument. At the center of the page Ukraine, with a service on the winning weapons of Kiev, drones on all. &nbsp;&nbsp;
